layer.title: Individual commands
layer.annotation: Goal: Pick an Alpine mirror for the `apk` package manager to use, and enable the community repository. Tools: Busybox's built-in Borne shell interpreter runs Alpine's `setup-apkrepos` script. Result: successResult
Goal: Change working directory to the current user's home directory. Tool: cd command (built into Busybox's shell) Result: successResult

Goal: Download the latest release of the Guile source distribution from GNU's public archive server. Tool: GNU wget Tool: Mistakes: Operator starts to tupe a `cd` command line out, poking around with tab-completion, before erasing the half-typed `cd` command and typing the `wget` command. Result: successResult

Goal: Extract the newly-downloaded `hello` Gzip-compressed source distribution tarball. Tool: The Mistake: A `-s` flag is mistakenly typed, but the mistake is corrected before finishing the prompt. Result: successResult
Goal: Descend into the newly-extracted `hello` source distribution directory. Tool: cd command (built into Busybox's shell) Result: successResult
Goal: Obtain a directory listing of the current working directory (the base of the downloaded `hello` source distribution) Tool: ls (built into the Busybox multi-call binary) Result: successResult

Goal: Configure the build system for `hello` so that it can be compiled and installed. Tool: Busybox's built-in shell interpreter running `hello`'s `configure` script. Discoveries: A working C compiler must be installed before `hello` can be built. Result: successFailure

Goal: Install the GNU C Compiler and the standard C library headers for the running Musl libC. Tool: The `apk` command's `add` subcommand Mistake: The user begins typing the `./configure` command before realizing that additional packages need to be installed first. Result: successResult

Goal: Configure the build system for `hello` so that it can be compiled and installed. Tool: Busybox's built-in shell interpreter running `hello`'s `configure` script. Discoveries: GNU make is required for `hello` to build. Result: successFailure
Goal: Install the GNU `make` package from an Alpine archive mirror. Tool: Alpine's `apk`'s `add` operation Result: successResult
Configure the build system for `hello` so that it can be compiled and installed. Tool: Busybox's built-in shell interpreter running `hello`'s `configure` script. Result: successResult
Goal: Build the newly-configured `hello` sources from the Guild source distribution. Tool: GNU `make` running the default target for the project. Result: successResult
Goal: Obtain a directory listing of the current working directory in hopes that a `hello` binary might be there. Tool: ls (built into the Busybox multi-call binary) Result: successResult
Goal: Test the newly-compiled `hello` program to see if it runs correctly. Tool: The `hello` binary program in the current working directory Result: successResult

Goal: See if the `hello` program lives up to its promise of having `help2man`-friendly help output. Tool: The `hello` program in the current working directory Discovery: There is a "-t" flag for a "traditional" greeting. Result: successResult
Goal: Test the newly-discovered "traditional" `hello` greeting mode. Tool: The `hello` program in the current working directory. Result: successResult
Goal: Install `hello` to the `configure`d `PREFIX`. Tool: GNU `make` running the `install` target. Result: successResult
Goal: Verify the presence of `hello` installed in the `configure`d `PREFIX` Tool: `which` command (built into the Busybox multi-call binary) Result: successResult
Goal: Check the version of the installed `hello`. Tool: GNU `hello` with its `--version` flag Result: successResult
Goal: Dump this shell's history to the terminal and a file at the path "/herstory" Tool: Alpine Linux. Subtool: Result: successResult
